"   </a>",
"  </div>",
" </div>",
" <div class=\"graphic\">",
"  <div class=\"figure\" style=\"width: 470px\">",
"   <div class=\"ttl\">",
"    Actinomyces",
"   </div>",
"   <div class=\"cntnt\" style=\"width: 365px; height: 240px; background-image: url(data:image/jpeg;base64,);\">",
"   </div>",
"   <div class=\"lgnd\">",
"    Gram stain of aspirate from oral abscess (x1000) shows abundant inflammatory cells and thin Gram positive, branching filaments consistent with either Actinomyces or Nocardia; the latter stains red on modified acid-fast stain, while the former does not. Actinomyces is frequently isolated from abscesses related to the oral cavity. A. israeli grew from this specimen.",
"    <div class=\"footnotes\">",
"    </div>",
"    <div class=\"reference\">",
"     Courtesy of Harriet Provine.",
"    </div>",
"   </div>",
"  </div>",
" </div>",
